location_guide:
About Destin

Destin is a world-class beach and fishing resort community, widely known as the "World's Luckiest Fishing Village". Destin is home to over 12,000 residents, providing entertainment for more than six times that many visitors during the summer. This charming beach community seeks to carefully balance quality of life for its residents and visitors, while preserving its rich heritage and environment. The area's warm summers and mild winters support a comfortable climate year round.

Destin is situated on Northwest Florida's captivating Emerald Coast, approximately 45 miles east of Pensacola and 55 miles west of Panama City. Local air transportation includes Northwest Florida Regional Airport (VPS), located about five miles north of Fort Walton Beach, and Destin Airport (DTS), located on Airport Road. Northwest Florida Beaches International Airport (ECP) is the first international airport to be built in the U.S. in more than a decade. ECP is located in West Bay, near Panama City and Panama City Beach.

Destin offers exceptional accommodations options. Whether for business, pleasure, or hosting out-of-town guests, there's a house, resort, or condominium to fit your needs. Emerald Grande, perched above the bustling HarborWalk Village, offers classic architecture and panoramic views of the Emerald Coast. Destin East Pass Towers Yacht Club is located on the very tip of Destin's Holiday Isle and offers stunning views of both the Destin Harbor and East Pass. The Terrace at Pelican Beach offers luxurious resort condominiums with plenty of room for families to enjoy time together.

Destin area restaurants are serving up culinary masterpieces created by award-winning chefs to tantalize your taste buds. Cuvee Bistro offers classic French, Asian and Mediterranean influenced delicacies along with signature dishes by proprietor and celebrity Chef Tim Creehan. Louisiana Lagniappe offers fresh seafood and steaks with a Creole flair in a casual, yet upscale waterfront dining experience. A favorite with Destin locals since 1974, The Back Porch Seafood & Oyster House serves delicious gulf seafood and claims to have "the best view in Destin".

Destin offers an array of activities and attractions for the whole family. The classic appeal of breathtaking beaches and stunning Gulf water is just the beginning. The area also offers plenty of shopping, nightspots, world-class fishing, golfing, recreational activities and more. A unique, open air town center, Destin Commons features upscale shopping and casual and fine dining. Harborwalk Village offers activities and entertainment for all ages including waterfront shopping, water sports, boat, pontoon and ski rentals, world class fishing, clubs and nightlife and an array of restaurants to satisfy all tastes. Big Kahuna's Water and Adventure Park offers more than 40 exciting water attractions, mini golf courses, two go kart tracks and adrenaline-pumping rides. And during the entire month of October, the Destin Fishing Rodeo gives both experienced and beginner fishermen (and women!) the opportunity to compete for cash and prizes.

Today, Destin draws visitors from across the nation to experience the magic of this breathtaking locale. By land or by water, the possibilities are endless in this exhilarating city.

Information provided by: Emerald Coast Convention & Visitors Bureau
